{"id":"confession","term":"Confession","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(1) An open profession of faith (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 12:8\">Luke 12:8</a>). (2.) An acknowledment of sins to God (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 16:21\">Lev. 16:21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezra 9:5\">Ezra 9:5-15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Daniel 9:3\">Dan. 9:3-12</a>), and to a neighbour whom we have wronged (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 5:16\">James 5:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 18:15\">Matt. 18:15</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Luke 12:8","Leviticus 16:21","Ezra 9:5","Daniel 9:3","James 5:16","Matthew 18:15"]}